{{afc comment|1=This article as with the other date articles is relatively limited in scope to Japan. Reviewing the translation of this is good and also adding content translated from Chinese and Korean wikipedias will also be good. Both wikipedias are also relatively centered around their own countries for their Lunisolar calendar dates[[User:Immanuelle|Immanuelle]] ([[User talk:Immanuelle|talk]]) 00:16, 28 April 2025 (UTC)}} {{Globalize|article|Japan|date=April 2025}} {{Expand Chinese|1=九月二十|topic=hist|date=April 2025}} {{Expand Korean|1=음력 9월 20일|topic=hist|date=April 2025}} {{Lunisolar September|qq=}} '''September 20''' is the 20th day of month {{ill|September (Lunisolar)|ja|9月 (旧暦)|lt=September (Nagatsuki)|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=}} the 9th month of the traditional {{ill|Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|ja|旧暦|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|11=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=}} . It's {{ill|Rokuyō|ja|六曜|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=}} day is {{ill|Butsumetsu|ja|仏滅|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=}} . == Events == * {{ill|Kenkou|ja|建光|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=}} 1st Year ({{ill|Julian calendar|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano|ja|ユリウス暦|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=}} {{ill|121|ja|121st year|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=}} {{ill|October 19|ja|10月19日|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=}} ) – The oldest Chinese dictionary, ''{{ill|Shuowen Jiezi|ja|説文解字|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=}} '', compiled by {{ill|Xu Shen|ja|許慎|lt=Xu Shen|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=}} , was presented to Emperor {{ill|An|ja|安帝|lt=Emperor An|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=}} of the Later Han. * {{ill|Bunji|ja|文治|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=}} 3rd Year ({{ill|Julian calendar|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano|ja|ユリウス暦|1=Julian calendar|