{{Not to be confused with|September 20 (Lunisolar)}}<!--hatnote--> {{afc comment|1=This article as with the other date articles is relatively limited in scope to Japan. Reviewing the translation of this is good and also adding content translated from Chinese and Korean wikipedias will also be good. Both wikipedias are also relatively centered around their own countries for their Lunisolar calendar dates[[User:Immanuelle|Immanuelle]] ([[User talk:Immanuelle|talk]]) 00:16, 28 April 2025 (UTC)}} {{Globalize|article|Japan|date=April 2025}} {{Expand Chinese|1=九月二十|topic=hist|date=April 2025}} {{Expand Korean|1=음력 9월 20일|topic=hist|date=April 2025}} {{Lunisolar September|qq=}} '''September 20''' is the 20th day of month {{ill|September (Lunisolar)|ja|9月 (旧暦)|lt=September (Nagatsuki)|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/September (Lunisolar)|qq=}} the 9th month of the traditional {{ill|Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|ja|旧暦|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|11=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|13=User:Immanuelle/Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|qq=}} . It's {{ill|Rokuyō|ja|六曜|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Rokuyō|qq=}} day is {{ill|Butsumetsu|ja|仏滅|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Butsumetsu|qq=}} . == Events == * {{ill|Kenkou|ja|建光|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kenkou|qq=}} 1st Year ([[:en:Julian calendar|Julian calendar]] [[:en:AD 121|121]] [[:en:October 19|October 19]] ) – The oldest Chinese dictionary, ''[[:en:Shuowen Jiezi|Shuowen Jiezi]] '', compiled by [[:en:Xu Shen|Xu Shen]] , was presented to Emperor [[:en:Emperor An|Emperor An]] of the Later Han. * [[:en:Bunji (era)|Bunji]] 3rd Year ([[:en:Julian calendar|Julian calendar]] [[:en:1187|1187]] [[:en:October 23|October 23]] ) – [[:en:Fujiwara no Shunzei|Fujiwara Toshinari]] presented the anthology ''[[:en:Senzai Wakashū|Senzaishū]] '' to {{ill|Emperor Go-Shirakawa|ja|後白河法皇|lt=Emperor Go-Shirakawa|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Emperor Go-Shirakawa|qq=}} . * [[:en:Gentoku|Gentoku]] 3rd Year / [[:en:Genkō (1331–1334)|Genkō]] 1st Year ([[:en:Julian calendar|Julian calendar]] [[:en:1331|1331]] [[:en:October 22|October 22]] ) – [[:en:Emperor Kōgon|Emperor Kōgon]] of the Northern Court ascended the throne. * [[:en:Bunna|Bunwa]] 2nd Year / [[:en:Zhengping|Shōhei]] 8th Year ([[:en:Julian calendar|Julian calendar]] [[:en:1353|1353]] [[:en:October 17|October 17]] ) – {{ill|Ashikaga Takauji|ja|Ashikaga Takauji|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ashikaga Takauji|qq=}} entered Kyoto, endorsing the authority of [[:en:Emperor Go-Kōgon|Emperor Gōkō]] . * [[:en:Meiji era|Meiji era]] 1st Year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[:en:1868|1868]] [[:en:November 4|November 4]] ) – Emperor [[:en:Emperor Meiji|Meiji]] departed Kyoto and headed for Tokyo.
== Births == * {{ill|Tenmon|ja|天文|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Tenmon|qq=}} 4th Year ([[:en:Julian calendar|Julian calendar]] [[:en:1535|1535]] [[:en:October 16|October 16]] ) – [[:en:Niwa Nagahide|Niwa Nagahide]] , a military commander (died [[:en:1585|1585]] ). * [[:en:Kaei|Kaei]] 5th Year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[:en:1852|1852]] [[:en:November 1|November 1]] ) – [[:en:Hon'inbō Shūei|Honinbo Shuei]] , a professional Go player (died [[:en:1907|1907]] ).
== Deaths == * {{ill|Genki|ja|Genki (era)|Genki|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Genki|qq=}} 1st Year ([[:en:Julian calendar|Julian calendar]] [[:en:1570|1570]] [[:en:October 19|October 19]] ) – [[:en:Mori Yoshinari|Mori Kanenari]] , a military commander (born [[:en:1523|1523]] ). * {{ill|Keichō|1=Keichō|2=ja|3=慶長|ja|Keichō|1=Keichō|2=ja|3=慶長|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Keichō|qq=}} 10th Year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[:en:1605|1605]] [[:en:November 1|November 1]] ) – [[:en:Yamauchi Kazutoyo|Yamauchi Kazutoyo]] , the first lord of the Tosa Domain (born [[:en:1546|1546]] ). * [[:en:Jōō (Edo period)|Shōō]] 3rd Year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[:en:1654|1654]] [[:en:October 30|October 30]] ) – [[:en:Emperor Go-Kōmyō|Emperor Gōmyō]] , the 110th Emperor (born [[:en:1633|1633]] ). * [[:en:Kyōhō|Kyōhō]] 15th Year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[:en:1730|1730]] [[:en:October 31|October 31]] ) – {{ill|Naka Jinbe|ja|中甚兵衛|lt=Naka Jinbe|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Naka Jinbe|qq=}} , a village head from Imaze Village in Kawachi Province who significantly contributed to the reorganization of work on the Yamato River (born [[:en:1639|1639]] ). * [[:en:Culture|Bunka]] 3rd Year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[:en:1806|1806]] [[:en:October 31|October 31]] ) – [[:en:Utamaro|Kitagawa Utamaro]] , an ukiyo-e artist (born [[:en:1753|1753]] ).
