peror An|Emperor An]] of the Later Han. * [[:en:Bunji (era)|Bunji]] 3rd Year ([[:en:Julian calendar|Julian calendar]] [[:en:1187|1187]] [[:en:October 23|October 23]] ) – [[:en:Fujiwara no Shunzei|Fujiwara Toshinari]] presented the anthology ''[[:en:Senzai Wakashū|Senzaishū]] '' to {{ill|Emperor Go-Shirakawa|ja|後白河法皇|lt=Emperor Go-Shirakawa|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Emperor Go-Shirakawa|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to 後白河天皇}} . * [[:en:Gentoku|Gentoku]] 3rd Year / [[:en:Genkō (1331–1334)|Genkō]] 1st Year ([[:en:Julian calendar|Julian calendar]] [[:en:1331|1331]] [[:en:October 22|October 22]] ) – [[:en:Emperor Kōgon|Emperor Kōgon]] of the Northern Court ascended the throne. * [[:en:Bunna|Bunwa]] 2nd Year / [[:en:Zhengping|Shōhei]] 8th Year ([[:en:Julian calendar|Julian calendar]] [[:en:1353|1353]] [[:en:October 17|October 17]] ) – {{ill|Ashikaga Takauji|ja|Ashikaga Takauji|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ashikaga Takauji|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}} entered Kyoto, endorsing the authority of [[:en:Emperor Go-Kōgon|Emperor Gōkō]] . * [[:en:Meiji era|Meiji era]] 1st Year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[:en:1868|1868]] [[:en:November 4|November 4]] ) – Emperor [[:en:Emperor Meiji|Meiji]] departed Kyoto and headed for Tokyo.
== Births == * {{ill|Tenmon|ja|天文|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Tenmon|qq=}} 4th Year ([[:en:Julian calendar|Julian calendar]] [[:en:1535|1535]] [[:en:October 16|October 16]] ) – [[:en:Niwa Nagahide|Niwa Nagahide]] , a military commander (died [[:en:1585|1585]] ). * [[:en:Kaei|Kaei]] 5th Year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[:en:1852|1852]] [[:en:November 1|November 1]] ) – [[:en:Hon'inbō Shūei|Honinbo Shuei]] , a professional Go player (died [[:en:1907|1907]] ).
== Deaths == * {{ill|Genki|ja|Genki (era)|Genki|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Genki|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}} 1st Year ([[:en:Julian calendar|Julian calendar]] [[:en:1570|1570]] [[:en:October 19|October 19]] ) – [[:en:Mori Yoshinari|Mori Kanenari]] , a military commander (born [[:en:1523|1523]] ). * [[:en:Keichō|Keichō]] 10th Year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[:en:1605|1605]] [[:en:November 1|November 1]] ) – [[:en:Yamauchi Kazutoyo|Yamauchi Kazutoyo]] , the first lord of the Tosa Domain (born [[:en:1546|1546]] ). * [[:en:Jōō (Edo period)|Shōō]] 3rd Year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[:en:1654|1654]] [[:en:October 30|October 30]] ) – [[:en:Emperor Go-Kōmyō|Emperor Gōmyō]] , the 110th Emperor (born [[:en:1633|1633]] ). * [[:en:Kyōhō|Kyōhō]] 15th Year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[:en:1730|1730]] [[:en:October 31|October 31]] ) – {{ill|Naka Jinbe|ja|中甚兵衛|lt=Naka Jinbe|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Naka Jinbe|qq=}} , a village head from Imaze Village in Kawachi Province who significantly contributed to the reorganization of work on the Yamato River (born [[:en:1639|1639]] ). * [[:en:Culture|Bunka]] 3rd Year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[:en:1806|1806]] [[:en:October 31|October 31]] ) – [[:en:Utamaro|Kitagawa Utamaro]] , an ukiyo-e artist (born [[:en:1753|1753]] ).
